{{see|Charity}}
==English==

===Pronunciation===
* [[w:IPA_chart_for_English|IPA]]: /tʃɛɹəti/, [[w:SAMPA/English|SAMPA]]: /tSEr@ti/.

===Etymology===
From late Old English, , from Old French ''[[charite]]'', from  Latin ''[[carus]]'' (dear). Early sense was 'Christian love of one's fellows'.

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg-y|charit|y}}

#''(uncountable)'' The providing of goods or money to those in need.
# The goods or money given to those in need.
#''(countable)'' An [[organization]] whose purpose is to provide for those in need.
# An [[attitude]] of kindness and understanding towards others.
#:'''quotation'''
#: Judge thyself with the judgment of sincerity, and thou will judge others with the judgment of '''charity'''. &mdash; ''John Mitchell Mason''

